text: On 30 July 2019, a Beechcraft King Air of the Pakistan Army crashed near Bahria Town, Rawalpindi. All five crew members, as well as 13 civilians, were killed when the plane crashed into a residential area. ==References== Army military plane crash Army military plane crash Category:Accidents and incidents involving military aircraft Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in 2019 Category:History of Rawalpindi Army military plane crash 2019 military plane crash
title: 2019 Pakistan Army military plane crash
